  $$n=\frac{z_\frac{\alpha}{2}^2 \times \hat{p} \times \hat{q}}{E^2}$$
  where $E$ is our target margin of error.</li>
  <li>Let's suppose that we want to conduct a survey to find the number of US adults that make online purchases of household goods but we do not have any estimate for $\hat{p}$ already.</li>
