    $$n =\frac{1.96^2 \times 0.5 \times 0.5}{0.0009} \approx 1068$$
    total samples.</li>
    <li>In this case the number of necessary samples went up, because we had to choose this conservatively without already knowing an estimate for <b style="color:#d95f02">$\hat{p}$</b>.</li>
